      "content": "To calculate the impact of higher shrinkage, you need to adjust your Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) by adding the value of the lost inventory. The standard Inventory Turnover Ratio is calculated as COGS divided by Average Inventory. By increasing the COGS to account for shrinkage, you will see a lower turnover ratio, which correctly reflects the reduced efficiency of your inventory management. This adjusted figure will clearly demonstrate the financial drag caused by the excess shrinkage to your manager.",
