      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you are correct; adding the shrinkage value to COGS will cause the inventory turnover ratio to decrease. This lower ratio signifies that you are moving through your inventory less efficiently due to the losses. You should keep the average inventory calculation as is, as it reflects the average *book* value while the adjusted COGS now accounts for the *actual* cost of goods that left your system, including the loss. This comparison clearly isolates the impact of the shrinkage on your performance metric.",
